"title": "7442: shrine",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7442",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A local sanctuary, often dedicated to pagan worship. Before the building of the temple the Israelites worshipped at several divinely sanctioned shrines; afterwards, worship at a central sanctuary was required. True worship of God required that pagan shrines be destroyed. It was Israel's failure to abandon these religious sites that led to syncretism and apostasy.</p>\n<h2>Common features of pagan shrines</h2>\n<h3>A location on high ground under trees</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek6:13\">EZK 6:13</a></strong> <em>Mountains were considered the dwelling- places of the gods, whilst trees were associated with fertility.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:10\">2KI 17:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:29\">ISA 1:29</a> <em>sacred trees</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:20\">JER 2:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek18:11\">EZK 18:11</a> <em>mountain shrines</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek20:28\">EZK 20:28</a></p>\n<h3>Idols and sacred symbols</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:13\">ISA 44:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs10:26-2Kgs10:27\">2KI 10:26–10:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:29-2Kgs17:31\">2KI 17:29–17:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr34:3-2Chr34:4\">2CH 34:3–34:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:24\">ACT 19:24</a></p>\n<h3>A serving priesthood</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:5\">2KI 23:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:20\">2KI 23:20</a></p>\n<h3>Sacrifice to the deity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer48:35\">JER 48:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:43\">1KI 22:43</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs12:3\">2KI 12:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs16:4\">2KI 16:4</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr28:4\">2CH 28:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr28:25\">2CH 28:25</a></p>\n<h3>Shrine-prostitution</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen38:21-Gen38:22\">GEN 38:21–38:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut23:17\">DEU 23:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs14:24\">1KI 14:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs15:12\">1KI 15:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job36:14\">JOB 36:14</a></p>\n<h2>Pagan shrines were to be destroyed</h2>\n<h3>On Israel's entry into Canaan</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut12:2-Deut12:3\">DEU 12:2–12:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:13-Exod34:14\">EXO 34:13–34:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num33:52\">NUM 33:52</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:5\">DEU 7:5</a></p>\n<h3>As a sign of religious reformation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:25\">JDG 6:25</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:8-2Kgs23:20\">2KI 23:8–23:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs10:25\">2KI 10:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr14:3\">2CH 14:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr17:6\">2CH 17:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs18:4\">2KI 18:4</a></p>\n<h2>Shrines in Israel for the worship of God</h2>\n<h3>Worship at the high places</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs3:2-1Kgs3:3\">1KI 3:2–3:3</a></strong> <em>Following Canaanite custom, Israel set up shrines on high ground possibly, against God's instruction, at old Baal sites. Worship at these non-legitimate sites was condemned.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr33:17\">2CH 33:17</a></p>\n<h3>Worship at sites sanctioned by God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:24\">EXO 20:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:22-Judg6:24\">JDG 6:22–6:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam9:12-1Sam9:14\">1SA 9:12–9:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:5\">1SA 10:5</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of shrines dedicated to God</h3>\n<p>Bethel:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:8\">GEN 12:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg21:2\">JDG 21:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh18:1\">JOS 18:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg21:19\">JDG 21:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg20:1\">JDG 20:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam7:6\">1SA 7:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs3:4-1Kgs3:5\">1KI 3:4–3:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:39-1Chr16:40\">1CH 16:39–16:40</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr1:13\">2CH 1:13</a></p>\n<h3>A central place of worship was later required</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs18:22\">2KI 18:22</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa36:7\">ISA 36:7</a> <em>Following the building of the temple, worship in various scattered shrines was condemned, probably because of associations with pagan worship.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut12:4-Deut12:7\">DEU 12:4–12:7</a> <em>The central sanctuary was, initially, the place where the tabernacle was located. Eventually this was superseded by the temple</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:13\">2SA 7:13</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr17:12\">1CH 17:12</a></p>\n<h2>Israel's failure to abandon worship at the shrines led to apostasy</h2>\n<h3>Improper worship at shrines dedicated to God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg17:5\">JDG 17:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg18:30-Judg18:31\">JDG 18:30–18:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:28-1Kgs12:31\">1KI 12:28–12:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs13:32\">1KI 13:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:32-2Kgs17:33\">2KI 17:32–17:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr11:15\">2CH 11:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos4:4\">AMO 4:4</a></p>\n<h3>The corruption of temple worship</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:4-2Kgs23:7\">2KI 23:4–23:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek8:14-Ezek8:16\">EZK 8:14–8:16</a></p>\n<h3>Shrines dedicated to false gods</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs14:23-1Kgs14:24\">1KI 14:23–14:24</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek8:12\">EZK 8:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:7-1Kgs11:8\">1KI 11:7–11:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs21:2-2Kgs21:3\">2KI 21:2–21:3</a>JER <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs7:31\">7:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer19:5\">JER 19:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer32:35\">JER 32:35</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:26\">AMO 5:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:43\">ACT 7:43</a></p>\n<h3>Israel's spiritual adultery</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:24-Ezek16:25\">EZK 16:24–16:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:6\">JER 3:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:39\">EZK 16:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek18:6\">EZK 18:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos4:12-Hos4:13\">HOS 4:12–4:13</a></p>\n<h3>God's judgment on false places of worship</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek6:3-Ezek6:6\">EZK 6:3–6:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:30-Lev26:31\">LEV 26:30–26:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos10:8\">HOS 10:8</a></p>",
